metadata.name: Making Space
metadata.description:
Düsseldorf, Germany 2018 - On the lively Rheinuferpromenade between the old town and the Rhein river in Düsseldorf, the day awoke with a cloud swallowing the city whole. Often crowded with the chatter of the city, it suddenly felt like a ghost town, with none but a lone traveler and his hovering birds. While capturing this photo, there was an exhilaration that gave me a sense of freedom and release. The trees aligned themselves to make space to leave the weight of the mundane behind.
